WEBVTT

00:00:06.065 --> 00:00:07.705
In this competition,

00:00:07.785 --> 00:00:08.945
withdrawals will not be allowed.

00:00:09.025 --> 00:00:10.505
I still don't trust Sarut.

00:00:10.585 --> 00:00:12.185
He might have another scheme up
his sleeve.

00:00:12.265 --> 00:00:13.545
How did he get in here?

00:00:13.625 --> 00:00:16.065
I'm sorry.
If we'd been able to stay in touch,

00:00:16.145 --> 00:00:17.625
you wouldn't have had to
go through all that alone.

00:00:18.625 --> 00:00:21.265
If you trick her into
becoming your friend with benefits,

00:00:21.345 --> 00:00:24.585
she'll only fall for you even more.

00:00:24.665 --> 00:00:26.505
Next time you're not feeling okay,

00:00:26.585 --> 00:00:28.705
why don't you try visiting an art gallery?

00:00:28.785 --> 00:00:29.905
Will you take me there?

00:00:31.065 --> 00:00:32.544
Song, don't be afraid.

00:00:32.625 --> 00:00:34.425
I'll be your dreamcatcher.

00:00:34.505 --> 00:00:36.465
Then don't push me away.

00:01:02.505 --> 00:01:04.305
Song, don't be afraid.

00:01:05.585 --> 00:01:07.905
I'll be your dreamcatcher.

00:01:28.385 --> 00:01:30.225
No.

00:01:31.305 --> 00:01:33.185
Stay a little longer.

00:01:33.785 --> 00:01:35.265
Where are you going?

00:01:39.745 --> 00:01:40.785
I'm heading home.

00:01:43.305 --> 00:01:44.985
Don't go just yet.

00:01:45.505 --> 00:01:46.905
Song.

00:01:48.385 --> 00:01:49.345
Song.

00:01:51.145 --> 00:01:52.585
Are you okay?

00:01:54.145 --> 00:01:55.065
This stupid bed.

00:01:59.945 --> 00:02:01.425
The bed didn't do anything.

00:02:01.505 --> 00:02:03.345
Why blame it?

00:02:06.945 --> 00:02:08.185
Are you hurt badly?

00:02:08.905 --> 00:02:10.105
Not really.

00:02:13.705 --> 00:02:15.065
Can you get up?

00:02:16.505 --> 00:02:17.385
I can.

00:02:21.745 --> 00:02:22.905
Sit down first.

00:02:31.665 --> 00:02:34.705
Song. Can you stay a bit longer?

00:02:34.785 --> 00:02:36.865
I worked so hard to lull you
to sleep last night.

00:02:36.945 --> 00:02:39.825
And let you use my arm
as a pillow until it went numb.

00:02:40.705 --> 00:02:42.185
So stay with me a little longer.

00:02:43.185 --> 00:02:44.745
I didn't ask you to do that.

00:02:49.265 --> 00:02:51.545
I need to get back to work.

00:02:51.625 --> 00:02:53.145
I need to test a recipe.

00:02:53.225 --> 00:02:54.745
So I can get into the lab on Monday

00:02:54.825 --> 00:02:56.105
and continue the process.

00:02:58.545 --> 00:03:01.585
Okay. Then I won't keep you any longer.

00:03:01.665 --> 00:03:04.785
I hope everything goes smoothly
with your work.

00:03:23.825 --> 00:03:24.825
I'm leaving now.

00:05:22.705 --> 00:05:24.625
What are you making?

00:05:24.705 --> 00:05:26.505
The aroma reached
all the way to the front gate.

00:05:27.225 --> 00:05:31.265
Well, I'm testing a recipe
for a competition, Grandma.

00:05:31.345 --> 00:05:33.785
And what are you making, dear?

00:05:33.865 --> 00:05:35.745
The smell seems familiar.

00:05:36.345 --> 00:05:38.065
Here's the thing, Grandma.

00:05:38.145 --> 00:05:40.145
The challenge from my boss is

00:05:40.225 --> 00:05:42.825
to create a dish
that captures the taste of love.

00:05:42.905 --> 00:05:45.545
That reminded me
of the porridge you used to make.

00:05:45.625 --> 00:05:46.905
Oh.

00:05:46.985 --> 00:05:50.185
But, I replaced rice with quinoa.

00:05:51.305 --> 00:05:52.505
for a healthier option.

00:05:54.505 --> 00:05:55.905
Very good.

00:05:55.985 --> 00:05:59.185
But, could you give it a taste for me?

00:05:59.265 --> 00:06:01.865
I want to know if it's as good as
the one you used to make.

00:06:01.945 --> 00:06:03.745
Of course, dear. Come here.

00:06:14.065 --> 00:06:16.025
Perfect.

00:06:16.105 --> 00:06:18.465
You're quite talented too.

00:06:20.465 --> 00:06:23.305
You're finally smiling,
my dear granddaughter.

00:06:23.825 --> 00:06:24.745
What?

00:06:25.345 --> 00:06:26.505
Before this,

00:06:26.585 --> 00:06:30.865
I could see that you've been feeling down.

00:06:30.945 --> 00:06:33.025
Did you and that girl have a fight?

00:06:33.105 --> 00:06:35.585
We didn't fight.
I just had something on my mind.

00:06:42.465 --> 00:06:44.865
I thought you said there was no one.

00:06:44.945 --> 00:06:47.345
Aha.

00:06:47.425 --> 00:06:50.065
Caught you now.

00:06:50.145 --> 00:06:51.985
Don't try to hide your
embarrassment from me.

00:06:52.065 --> 00:06:54.665
Do you know

00:06:54.745 --> 00:06:57.465
how happy I am to see you

00:06:57.545 --> 00:07:00.385
open your heart again?

00:07:03.345 --> 00:07:04.385
Here.

00:07:17.425 --> 00:07:18.825
Have you eaten yet?

00:07:32.825 --> 00:07:34.265
Have you eaten yet?

00:07:37.945 --> 00:07:39.985
I'm eating the dessert you made for me.

00:07:40.065 --> 00:07:42.065
It's really delicious.

00:07:47.065 --> 00:07:49.905
If you say that, I'll want
to cook for you every day.

00:07:51.745 --> 00:07:53.385
Then it wouldn't be special anymore.

00:08:00.065 --> 00:08:00.905
Why not?

00:08:04.545 --> 00:08:06.265
Because special things

00:08:06.345 --> 00:08:08.705
become ordinary if you
have them every day.

00:08:08.785 --> 00:08:12.105
I want you to stay special
to me for a long time.

00:08:18.985 --> 00:08:19.865
Neung.

00:08:29.425 --> 00:08:30.305
Neung.

00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:31.505
What happened?

00:08:36.945 --> 00:08:37.985
What's wrong?

00:08:40.904 --> 00:08:42.065
Song.

00:08:42.985 --> 00:08:45.025
I feel like my partner has changed.

00:08:46.745 --> 00:08:47.945
It's like

00:08:48.825 --> 00:08:50.905
they're seeing someone else.

00:08:56.625 --> 00:08:57.825
It's okay.

00:08:57.905 --> 00:08:59.265
Don't cry.

00:09:03.785 --> 00:09:05.385
I'm here with you now.

00:09:05.985 --> 00:09:06.905
Take it easy.

00:09:16.745 --> 00:09:18.465
Come here, Moo Grob.

00:09:19.145 --> 00:09:21.225
Where are you going? Come here.

00:09:25.905 --> 00:09:27.745
HAVE YOU EATEN YET?

00:09:29.385 --> 00:09:31.785
Why isn't she replying?

00:10:04.465 --> 00:10:05.825
Hello, what's up?

00:10:05.905 --> 00:10:09.185
Mon, is your plan really going to work?

00:10:09.265 --> 00:10:11.145
Things seemed to be going well last night.

00:10:11.225 --> 00:10:14.185
But after we parted this morning,
she went quiet again.

00:10:14.785 --> 00:10:16.265
I texted her, but she didn't reply.

00:10:16.345 --> 00:10:18.145
Who told you to text her?

00:10:18.225 --> 00:10:19.545
Did you forget?

00:10:19.625 --> 00:10:21.985
What kind of relationship you two are in?

00:10:22.065 --> 00:10:24.825
You two are just friends with benefits.

00:10:24.905 --> 00:10:27.425
If she's being distant, you should be too.

00:10:27.505 --> 00:10:30.025
Don't contact her at all.

00:10:30.105 --> 00:10:32.825
You need to give her space to miss you.

00:10:33.985 --> 00:10:36.025
But I already miss her.

00:10:36.105 --> 00:10:38.665
Why do I have to force myself like this?

00:10:39.705 --> 00:10:41.545
Come on, be patient.

00:10:41.625 --> 00:10:43.145
Trust me.

00:10:43.225 --> 00:10:45.385
The result will be worth it.

00:10:48.745 --> 00:10:49.905
Fine.

00:10:49.985 --> 00:10:51.545
I'll endure it.

00:10:51.625 --> 00:10:54.465
Even when Song's
being rough on me, I can handle it.

00:10:54.545 --> 00:10:56.385
Why am I stressing over this?

00:10:57.225 --> 00:10:58.305
Oh, you.

00:10:58.385 --> 00:11:01.025
That's completely different.
How can you compare them?

00:11:01.105 --> 00:11:02.825
I'm done talking to you.

00:11:02.905 --> 00:11:04.265
I'm going back to work.

00:11:11.945 --> 00:11:14.345
I can't handle this.

00:11:28.305 --> 00:11:30.105
Dessert for Stress Relief.

00:11:37.505 --> 00:11:39.145
Chocolate muffins?

00:11:39.225 --> 00:11:40.745
INGREDIENTS

00:11:40.825 --> 00:11:41.985
SUGAR - SALT

00:12:39.465 --> 00:12:40.465
Ouch.

00:12:45.985 --> 00:12:47.345
This looks delicious.

00:12:56.025 --> 00:12:57.225
Morning, Song.

00:12:57.305 --> 00:12:58.305
Morning.

00:13:09.305 --> 00:13:10.905
Did you buy a new phone?

00:13:12.465 --> 00:13:13.865
No. I didn't buy it.

00:13:13.945 --> 00:13:15.145
Someone gave it to me.

00:13:17.785 --> 00:13:18.905
Who?

00:13:18.985 --> 00:13:20.105
That's so generous.

00:13:22.185 --> 00:13:24.425
Didn't you say your phone
was broken last night?

00:13:25.465 --> 00:13:26.745
Then why didn't you buy a new one?

00:13:26.825 --> 00:13:28.065
I just didn't need one.

00:13:29.425 --> 00:13:31.185
I only use it to contact people at work.

00:13:31.265 --> 00:13:33.785
And we see each other every day anyway.

00:13:34.305 --> 00:13:36.105
I was going to buy one after payday.

00:13:37.465 --> 00:13:39.465
You talk like there's no one
who cares about you.

00:13:39.545 --> 00:13:41.265
What about your family?

00:13:43.225 --> 00:13:44.345
There isn't any.

00:13:46.865 --> 00:13:48.305
I'm an orphan.

00:13:49.625 --> 00:13:51.425
I grew up in an orphanage.

00:13:52.185 --> 00:13:53.825
I don't have parents.

00:13:54.425 --> 00:13:57.825
I don't have any relatives either.

00:13:59.785 --> 00:14:00.985
But I'm okay.

00:14:03.225 --> 00:14:06.825
And don't say there's no one.

00:14:10.625 --> 00:14:11.585
I care about you.

00:14:32.305 --> 00:14:34.025
This is my spare phone.

00:14:34.105 --> 00:14:35.145
Use it for now.

00:14:35.825 --> 00:14:37.305
So whenever you're worried about me,

00:14:38.145 --> 00:14:39.705
you won't have to secretly check on me.

00:14:40.625 --> 00:14:44.145
Otherwise, the security guards
might think you're a scammer.

00:14:46.785 --> 00:14:49.345
Thank you for the phone.

00:14:50.105 --> 00:14:53.225
And, thank you
for letting me care about you.

00:14:54.945 --> 00:14:55.865
Hmm.

00:14:58.265 --> 00:15:00.545
The phone case is a little too flashy.

00:15:00.625 --> 00:15:02.425
If you don't like it, you can change it.

00:15:03.425 --> 00:15:04.625
Why wouldn't I like it?

00:15:06.225 --> 00:15:07.825
I love it.

00:15:08.785 --> 00:15:12.225
Flashy things like this
are totally my style.

00:15:14.705 --> 00:15:16.225
I've got something even flashier.

00:15:17.305 --> 00:15:18.385
Want to see it?

00:15:20.065 --> 00:15:21.585
Of course.

00:15:21.665 --> 00:15:22.785
Show me.

00:15:58.345 --> 00:15:59.505
Ple.

00:16:02.105 --> 00:16:03.865
Would you like to try dating me?

00:16:12.945 --> 00:16:14.145
I know

00:16:14.225 --> 00:16:17.225
you have painful memories
about your parents.

00:16:17.305 --> 00:16:19.025
That's why you don't want to date anyone.

00:16:20.545 --> 00:16:22.225
But look at me.

00:16:23.185 --> 00:16:25.705
My parents didn't even want me to be born.

00:16:28.185 --> 00:16:29.305
If we're comparing,

00:16:31.385 --> 00:16:32.905
I probably hurt more than you.

00:16:41.145 --> 00:16:43.065
But I've never let what they did

00:16:43.145 --> 00:16:45.065
become a condition for how I live my life.

00:16:46.065 --> 00:16:49.425
I just chose to let them go
so I could live the life I want.

00:16:56.505 --> 00:16:58.305
I don't want to stay stuck in the past.

00:17:00.985 --> 00:17:02.825
I want to be happy in the present.

00:17:04.464 --> 00:17:06.625
Try believing what I believe.

00:17:16.345 --> 00:17:17.345
Fine.

00:17:21.625 --> 00:17:22.905
I'll give it a try.

00:18:03.585 --> 00:18:04.665
Wow, Ple.

00:18:05.745 --> 00:18:07.705
I wondered how long she'd hold out.

00:18:07.785 --> 00:18:10.425
In the end, she fell for my little sister.

00:18:11.425 --> 00:18:14.465
Love isn't about winning or losing.

00:18:14.545 --> 00:18:16.025
It's about courage.

00:18:16.785 --> 00:18:19.745
Ple was brave enough
to move on from her past.

00:18:21.345 --> 00:18:22.665
What about you?

00:18:23.225 --> 00:18:24.705
Why not be brave too?

00:18:32.465 --> 00:18:35.985
I can tell things between you
and Piang aren't over.

00:18:37.065 --> 00:18:40.345
And there must be something
holding you back from moving forward.

00:18:41.105 --> 00:18:42.665
But trust me.

00:18:42.745 --> 00:18:45.465
-No matter what happens,
-It's far worse than you think.

00:18:47.065 --> 00:18:49.425
If you knew what it was,
you wouldn't be saying that.

00:18:51.105 --> 00:18:52.465
I'll get going now.

00:19:18.945 --> 00:19:22.025
Love isn't about winning or losing.

00:19:22.105 --> 00:19:24.185
It's about courage.

00:19:24.265 --> 00:19:27.305
Ple was brave enough
to move on from her past.

00:19:27.985 --> 00:19:29.785
What about you?

00:19:29.865 --> 00:19:31.465
Why not be brave too?

00:19:33.825 --> 00:19:35.305
Song.

00:19:36.425 --> 00:19:37.425
Yes?

00:19:39.345 --> 00:19:41.945
I've seen how hard you've been
preparing for the competition.

00:19:42.025 --> 00:19:45.585
So I bought your favorite
matcha to cheer you up.

00:19:46.905 --> 00:19:49.025
How did you know I like matcha?

00:19:49.105 --> 00:19:51.425
Because I like you.

00:19:51.505 --> 00:19:53.465
Of course I did my homework

00:19:53.545 --> 00:19:55.225
to find out what you like.

00:20:03.865 --> 00:20:05.985
Umm…

00:20:08.905 --> 00:20:09.945
These girls.

00:20:10.025 --> 00:20:11.865
How dare they mess with my Song.

00:20:11.945 --> 00:20:13.305
Just wait.

00:20:13.385 --> 00:20:14.665
You'll see.

00:20:15.665 --> 00:20:16.785
Please take it.

00:20:16.865 --> 00:20:19.225
Well, I…

00:20:22.225 --> 00:20:23.385
Piang.

00:20:25.745 --> 00:20:27.305
Yes, that's me.

00:20:27.385 --> 00:20:29.185
And are you trying to court Song?

00:20:30.305 --> 00:20:31.545
What did you say?

00:20:33.385 --> 00:20:35.425
Yes. Why?

00:20:36.465 --> 00:20:37.665
You should give up.

00:20:37.745 --> 00:20:38.905
Huh?

00:20:38.985 --> 00:20:40.945
And why is that any of your business?

00:20:41.545 --> 00:20:43.105
Why can't it be my business?

00:20:43.745 --> 00:20:45.065
I'm the chairwoman's granddaughter,

00:20:45.145 --> 00:20:47.585
and I'm also a shareholder
of this company.

00:20:47.665 --> 00:20:49.065
I don't like it

00:20:49.145 --> 00:20:52.585
when employees we pay every month
don't earn their salary

00:20:52.665 --> 00:20:55.625
because they're too busy
flirting with coworkers.

00:20:59.385 --> 00:21:02.345
But it's not working hours yet.

00:21:03.105 --> 00:21:05.185
Have you checked the time?

00:21:09.265 --> 00:21:11.145
It seems you only have the title,

00:21:11.225 --> 00:21:13.305
but know nothing about the company.

00:21:13.385 --> 00:21:15.505
You don't even know what time work starts.

00:21:16.345 --> 00:21:20.505
In that case, it'll be hard for us
to take you seriously.

00:21:26.745 --> 00:21:29.105
But I think you should listen.

00:21:29.185 --> 00:21:31.505
Even if it's not working hours yet,

00:21:31.585 --> 00:21:33.785
as fellow employees,

00:21:33.865 --> 00:21:35.865
we should respect the company.

00:21:35.945 --> 00:21:39.025
If it's not work-related,
we shouldn't be doing it.

00:21:40.185 --> 00:21:41.905
Thank you for the matcha,

00:21:41.985 --> 00:21:43.665
but you don't need to go
through the trouble next time.

00:21:43.745 --> 00:21:44.985
I can buy it myself.

00:21:51.905 --> 00:21:53.305
Enjoy it.

00:22:00.825 --> 00:22:01.865
That's enough.

00:22:03.625 --> 00:22:04.785
Let's talk.

00:22:16.465 --> 00:22:18.825
I thought we agreed
not to do this anymore.

00:22:18.905 --> 00:22:19.945
You wouldn't keep following me.

00:22:20.545 --> 00:22:21.825
I'm not following you.

00:22:22.545 --> 00:22:23.545
I just

00:22:23.625 --> 00:22:26.465
made some desserts to sell at my café.

00:22:26.545 --> 00:22:28.185
So I brought some for you to try.

00:22:28.265 --> 00:22:29.825
Then what was that just now?

00:22:30.825 --> 00:22:31.665
There you go again.

00:22:32.385 --> 00:22:34.825
Do you really want people
looking down on you?

00:22:36.585 --> 00:22:38.065
Are you worried about me?

00:22:43.665 --> 00:22:44.665
No.

00:22:45.225 --> 00:22:47.185
I just want you to understand

00:22:47.265 --> 00:22:49.665
that when you break our agreement,

00:22:49.745 --> 00:22:51.585
it affects you too.

00:22:52.465 --> 00:22:53.425
Just remember,

00:22:53.505 --> 00:22:56.505
don't do it again or this ends here.

00:23:00.145 --> 00:23:01.425
Wait.

00:23:01.505 --> 00:23:03.665
What? I thought I made myself clear.

00:23:04.345 --> 00:23:05.905
The desserts.

00:23:08.065 --> 00:23:10.465
Try them and don't forget
to give me your feedback.

00:23:24.425 --> 00:23:25.465
They smell amazing.

00:23:26.305 --> 00:23:28.625
These are definitely going to be good.

00:23:40.585 --> 00:23:41.985
Song.

00:23:42.065 --> 00:23:45.025
It worked. After reducing
the water like you suggested,

00:23:45.105 --> 00:23:46.065
the texture is perfect.

00:23:46.145 --> 00:23:47.705
-Wow.
-Look.

00:23:49.585 --> 00:23:50.705
Namprow, try it.

00:23:50.785 --> 00:23:51.945
-You want me to try it?
-Try it.

00:23:55.585 --> 00:23:58.225
Amazing. The texture is soft and silky.

00:23:58.305 --> 00:24:00.025
It's a ready-to-eat product.

00:24:00.105 --> 00:24:02.825
-Amazing. Great job.
-Amazing.

00:24:02.905 --> 00:24:05.545
-Yes.
-Yes. Yay!

00:24:05.625 --> 00:24:06.905
I give it a ten.

00:24:07.625 --> 00:24:08.625
Wow.

00:24:09.705 --> 00:24:12.465
Then there's nothing left to worry about.

00:24:13.065 --> 00:24:15.585
Now we just wait for competition day.

00:24:17.505 --> 00:24:19.385
-So exciting.
-Yeah.

00:24:19.465 --> 00:24:20.745
Are you guys hungry?

00:24:21.425 --> 00:24:22.745
Let's go get something to eat.

00:24:22.825 --> 00:24:24.185
My treat.

00:24:24.705 --> 00:24:27.585
Oops. There's something
I need to tell you.

00:24:27.665 --> 00:24:30.265
I really can't go with you today.

00:24:30.345 --> 00:24:34.065
I have a date with a guy.

00:24:35.145 --> 00:24:37.145
-What's that called again?
-Flexing.

00:24:37.225 --> 00:24:38.665
Exactly. Flexing. So today,

00:24:38.745 --> 00:24:40.425
-let me flex for once.
-She's funny.

00:24:40.945 --> 00:24:42.785
-Haha.
-I can't even.

00:24:42.865 --> 00:24:43.945
It's okay, Song.

00:24:44.025 --> 00:24:45.665
-Let's just go, the two of us.
-Yeah.

00:24:45.745 --> 00:24:48.465
It's not often an older
woman gets lucky with a man.

00:24:49.225 --> 00:24:50.465
Let's not get in her way.

00:24:50.545 --> 00:24:52.025
Sure, Miss Gen Z.

00:24:52.105 --> 00:24:53.785
Miss Queen Bee.

00:24:54.785 --> 00:24:56.705
Go ahead and tease me.

00:24:56.785 --> 00:24:58.065
You two should stop arguing.

00:25:00.025 --> 00:25:02.145
Let me check myself first.
I'm going on a date.

00:25:03.545 --> 00:25:04.545
Come on, let me help.

00:25:04.625 --> 00:25:06.865
I did my makeup in a
Chinese beauty style today.

00:25:06.945 --> 00:25:09.265
-Am I pretty? Here, look at yourself.
-You look great.

00:25:11.065 --> 00:25:12.625
Oh, you're pretty too.

00:25:12.705 --> 00:25:14.065
But I'm prettier today.

00:25:15.145 --> 00:25:17.585
Ploy, are we done for the day?

00:25:17.665 --> 00:25:19.225
I'm going to secretly check on Song.

00:25:22.145 --> 00:25:23.185
Song.

00:25:23.265 --> 00:25:24.905
I can't go with you after all.

00:25:24.985 --> 00:25:26.385
Ple texted and said she wants to see me.

00:25:27.465 --> 00:25:28.665
Alright, go ahead.

00:25:28.745 --> 00:25:30.025
I'm heading out too.

00:25:30.985 --> 00:25:33.105
Good luck. Bye.

00:25:33.185 --> 00:25:34.825
-Let's go. See you.
-Ple?

00:25:34.905 --> 00:25:37.105
Which Ple? Why don't I know her?

00:25:37.185 --> 00:25:38.465
See you. My date is waiting.

00:25:38.545 --> 00:25:41.825
-Let's go.
-I'm old. I'm old already.

00:25:41.905 --> 00:25:42.865
Be careful with me.

00:25:42.945 --> 00:25:45.225
I'm very fragile these days.

00:25:45.305 --> 00:25:47.545
-If my body gets ruined or bruised?
-Go now.

00:25:47.625 --> 00:25:48.945
That's not okay.

00:25:54.625 --> 00:25:55.585
It's just me then.

00:26:22.425 --> 00:26:25.905
Eating chocolate helps your body
release happiness hormones.

00:26:25.985 --> 00:26:28.385
I made these for you,
so you won't be stressed.

00:26:28.465 --> 00:26:30.985
And won't feel pressured
about the competition.

00:26:31.065 --> 00:26:33.025
And most importantly,

00:26:33.105 --> 00:26:34.705
you won't have nightmares anymore.

00:26:55.185 --> 00:26:56.065
Song.

00:27:02.865 --> 00:27:04.065
Are you hurt?

00:27:11.665 --> 00:27:14.665
How many times have I told
you not to follow me or spy on me?

00:27:14.745 --> 00:27:16.265
If someone sees you,
it'll cause trouble again.

00:27:17.145 --> 00:27:18.745
Please don't scold me yet.

00:27:18.825 --> 00:27:20.785
Let me treat your wound first.

00:27:21.505 --> 00:27:23.345
Where's the first aid kit?

00:27:27.785 --> 00:27:29.705
Stay out of it. That's enough.

00:27:37.265 --> 00:27:38.585
You never listen, do you?

00:27:39.465 --> 00:27:40.985
It's not that I don't listen.

00:27:41.065 --> 00:27:43.105
I wasn't spying on you.

00:27:43.185 --> 00:27:45.225
The reason I came here was…

00:27:51.025 --> 00:27:52.905
I came to get your
feedback on the desserts.

00:27:52.985 --> 00:27:54.145
Liar.

00:27:54.665 --> 00:27:56.545
I know that's not the only reason.

00:27:56.625 --> 00:27:58.025
Stop making excuses.

00:28:10.065 --> 00:28:11.065
Okay.

00:28:11.145 --> 00:28:13.065
I admit I was making excuses.

00:28:13.145 --> 00:28:14.345
I've been making excuses about everything.

00:28:15.665 --> 00:28:17.025
Even the friends with benefits thing,

00:28:17.105 --> 00:28:19.625
I used it as an excuse
to stay close to you.

00:28:20.985 --> 00:28:23.465
I'm not attached to you just
because of what happened in bed.

00:28:24.465 --> 00:28:26.625
I like everything about you.

00:28:34.065 --> 00:28:37.065
I like you a lot,
and I keep liking you more.

00:28:37.865 --> 00:28:40.265
To the point where I
can almost call it love.

00:28:43.145 --> 00:28:46.025
I can tell that you feel
something for me too.

00:28:47.705 --> 00:28:51.105
If we stay close,
no matter what our status is,

00:28:51.185 --> 00:28:53.385
one day you'll give in to me.

00:28:54.705 --> 00:28:55.545
Really?

00:28:58.585 --> 00:29:00.185
I'm glad you admitted it.

00:29:01.065 --> 00:29:02.225
Now listen to me.

00:29:02.785 --> 00:29:04.465
I'm only going to say this once more.

00:29:06.545 --> 00:29:08.665
I've never had feelings for you.

00:29:09.185 --> 00:29:10.345
Not once.

00:29:12.145 --> 00:29:13.425
-That's not true.
-It is.

00:29:13.945 --> 00:29:16.025
And no matter how hard you try,

00:29:16.105 --> 00:29:17.825
I'll never give in.

00:29:19.305 --> 00:29:20.305
I don't believe you.

00:29:42.505 --> 00:29:44.185
Just let me go.

00:29:45.385 --> 00:29:47.625
Don't hurt yourself any more than this.

00:30:37.905 --> 00:30:39.065
Now listen to me.

00:30:39.585 --> 00:30:41.385
I'm only going to say this once more.

00:30:42.505 --> 00:30:44.145
I've never had feelings for you.

00:30:45.105 --> 00:30:46.265
Not once.

00:30:46.345 --> 00:30:48.425
And no matter how hard you try,

00:30:48.505 --> 00:30:50.425
I'll never give in.

00:31:39.265 --> 00:31:40.305
Where are you?

00:31:40.825 --> 00:31:41.985
Are you heading home yet?

00:31:44.505 --> 00:31:46.185
I'm on my way home.

00:31:47.785 --> 00:31:48.665
Hey.

00:31:49.425 --> 00:31:50.665
Drive safely.

00:31:51.345 --> 00:31:52.465
I'm worried about you.

00:31:53.905 --> 00:31:55.585
You can call me if you need anything.

00:32:00.865 --> 00:32:01.865
Okay.

00:32:39.065 --> 00:32:40.745
Have you been waiting long?

00:32:42.905 --> 00:32:44.345
Not at all.

00:32:44.425 --> 00:32:46.705
I'm sorry for asking you to meet here.

00:32:46.785 --> 00:32:49.465
All the art galleries were already closed.

00:32:49.545 --> 00:32:51.745
So I didn't know where else to take you.

00:32:52.505 --> 00:32:53.865
That's okay.

00:32:53.945 --> 00:32:57.025
It's my fault.
I invited you out so suddenly.

00:33:02.025 --> 00:33:03.345
The mosquitoes got you good.

00:33:04.105 --> 00:33:05.025
Put on some repellent.

00:33:29.465 --> 00:33:31.385
You actually carry this around with you?

00:33:34.105 --> 00:33:36.865
Yeah, I come here pretty often.

00:33:37.505 --> 00:33:39.185
Even though I know there
are tons of mosquitoes.

00:33:40.385 --> 00:33:41.505
It's because

00:33:42.065 --> 00:33:43.665
I'm hooked on that grilled meatball stall.

00:33:47.745 --> 00:33:49.185
GRILLED MEATBALL
TEN BAHT EACH

00:33:49.265 --> 00:33:50.505
That's a lot of smoke.

00:33:51.905 --> 00:33:53.865
It must be really good.

00:33:54.385 --> 00:33:56.385
Not just good.

00:33:56.465 --> 00:33:58.785
It's freaking delicious.

00:34:04.065 --> 00:34:05.225
What are you laughing at?

00:34:06.105 --> 00:34:07.305
Well,

00:34:07.385 --> 00:34:10.105
I'm smiling because
you're being more yourself.

00:34:10.185 --> 00:34:13.145
Usually, you seem

00:34:13.225 --> 00:34:14.744
tense whenever you're around me.

00:34:20.065 --> 00:34:21.225
Come on.

00:34:21.744 --> 00:34:23.145
Let's go get some meatballs.

00:34:23.225 --> 00:34:25.945
I want to find out if they're

00:34:26.025 --> 00:34:27.905
really as freaking delicious as you said.

00:34:29.065 --> 00:34:29.905
Let's go.

00:34:45.105 --> 00:34:46.425
Not bad at all.

00:34:48.865 --> 00:34:51.545
So? Freaking delicious?

00:34:53.744 --> 00:34:54.744
Freaking delicious.

00:35:07.945 --> 00:35:09.185
By the way,

00:35:09.905 --> 00:35:11.425
the reason you called me here,

00:35:11.985 --> 00:35:13.745
is something wrong?

00:35:15.345 --> 00:35:16.345
Well,

00:35:17.465 --> 00:35:18.545
it's my younger sister.

00:35:20.505 --> 00:35:22.665
It looks like she's having some problems.

00:35:23.265 --> 00:35:24.625
But I

00:35:25.265 --> 00:35:27.225
don't seem able to help her at all.

00:35:27.745 --> 00:35:30.785
So, I've been stressing out
along with her.

00:35:31.545 --> 00:35:32.705
And,

00:35:32.785 --> 00:35:34.945
what did she tell you?

00:35:35.025 --> 00:35:37.545
Or maybe, did she ask you for help?

00:35:38.905 --> 00:35:41.825
Not at all. I think
she doesn't want to burden me.

00:35:43.785 --> 00:35:47.305
Or maybe she wants to solve it herself.

00:35:48.305 --> 00:35:49.625
I don't think so.

00:35:50.225 --> 00:35:51.625
Ever since we were kids,

00:35:51.705 --> 00:35:53.705
I've always been there to help her.

00:35:53.785 --> 00:35:56.665
I've never seen her solve
a problem on her own.

00:36:01.065 --> 00:36:04.385
Then you should let her try this time.

00:36:05.465 --> 00:36:07.905
Because if she can do it this time,

00:36:08.865 --> 00:36:10.185
from now on,

00:36:10.265 --> 00:36:12.465
you won't have to worry about her anymore.

00:36:13.465 --> 00:36:16.345
But if she really can't handle it,

00:36:16.945 --> 00:36:18.945
you can help her later.

00:36:19.025 --> 00:36:19.945
It won't be too late.

00:36:26.745 --> 00:36:28.065
You're right.

00:36:29.025 --> 00:36:33.025
Maybe I've been carrying
too much of her burden myself.

00:36:33.105 --> 00:36:34.505
I forgot

00:36:34.585 --> 00:36:37.945
that I should let her
try living her own life.

00:36:39.865 --> 00:36:41.145
It's strange.

00:36:41.225 --> 00:36:42.865
Just a few words from you,

00:36:42.945 --> 00:36:44.625
and I already feel so much lighter.

00:36:58.625 --> 00:36:59.785
Usually,

00:37:00.305 --> 00:37:03.225
you don't really talk to anyone, do you?

00:37:25.545 --> 00:37:27.185
Come in.

00:37:38.985 --> 00:37:40.345
Are you crying?

00:37:41.025 --> 00:37:41.985
No.

00:37:42.585 --> 00:37:45.265
My eyes just sting.

00:37:45.345 --> 00:37:46.985
I think some dust got in them.

00:37:50.105 --> 00:37:51.065
Alright.

00:37:51.145 --> 00:37:52.185
Good.

00:37:52.865 --> 00:37:55.425
Because I don't like seeing
my granddaughter weak.

00:37:58.225 --> 00:37:59.865
On the day your café opened,

00:37:59.945 --> 00:38:03.025
Dr. Namking came to congratulate you.

00:38:03.105 --> 00:38:06.065
After that, did you keep in touch?

00:38:08.025 --> 00:38:08.905
Not at all.

00:38:13.465 --> 00:38:15.705
Please don't be upset with her, Grandma.

00:38:15.785 --> 00:38:17.305
She must be really busy.

00:38:17.385 --> 00:38:20.025
I'm sure she'll contact me
when she's free.

00:38:20.105 --> 00:38:23.465
Then why don't you contact her first?

00:38:24.825 --> 00:38:26.785
If I did that,

00:38:27.505 --> 00:38:30.465
how would it be any different
from chasing after Song?

00:38:32.185 --> 00:38:35.265
I thought you didn't like me doing that.

00:38:35.345 --> 00:38:36.345
It's different.

00:38:36.425 --> 00:38:39.545
Pursuing someone on your level

00:38:39.625 --> 00:38:41.345
is at least worth it.

00:38:41.425 --> 00:38:43.065
No need to wait.

00:38:43.145 --> 00:38:45.385
Tomorrow is her birthday.

00:38:45.465 --> 00:38:47.745
Her grandmother is throwing her a party.

00:38:47.825 --> 00:38:50.465
You can take that chance to go see her.

00:38:55.265 --> 00:38:56.185
Okay.

00:39:17.225 --> 00:39:19.785
Who is the gift for, Grandma?

00:39:19.865 --> 00:39:22.145
It's for Dr. Namking, dear.

00:39:22.225 --> 00:39:25.625
This doctor treated my heart
condition before.

00:39:25.705 --> 00:39:28.945
It's good you're here. I need a favor.

00:39:29.025 --> 00:39:32.105
Tomorrow is Dr. Namking's birthday,

00:39:32.185 --> 00:39:34.865
and I heard that her grandmother

00:39:34.945 --> 00:39:36.785
is throwing her a birthday party.

00:39:36.865 --> 00:39:38.465
-Of course.
-Thank you.

00:39:38.545 --> 00:39:41.185
But I've never met her before.

00:39:41.265 --> 00:39:42.505
Do you have a photo of her?

00:39:42.585 --> 00:39:44.425
-Could I see it?
-Sure.

00:39:44.505 --> 00:39:46.105
Of course. Here.

00:39:46.185 --> 00:39:48.225
Let me show you.

00:39:52.065 --> 00:39:53.745
Here she is.

00:39:53.825 --> 00:39:55.585
Dr. Namking.

00:39:55.665 --> 00:39:58.825
She's very talented, you know.

00:39:58.905 --> 00:40:02.105
There are so many people in line,
getting an appointment isn't easy.

00:40:09.825 --> 00:40:11.985
She's very talented

00:40:12.745 --> 00:40:14.945
Patients keep coming to her.

00:40:15.025 --> 00:40:17.225
She's tall and slender.
You remember her face, right?

00:40:29.985 --> 00:40:32.385
Go greet your guests. Don't mind me.

00:40:32.465 --> 00:40:34.145
-I'll go with you.
-Okay.

00:40:34.985 --> 00:40:37.545
-You two have a chat.
-Okay.

00:40:37.625 --> 00:40:39.905
-Take care of Piang for me.
-Sure.

00:40:39.985 --> 00:40:41.065
-Go on and talk, dear.
-Okay.

00:40:42.665 --> 00:40:43.665
Alright.

00:40:47.465 --> 00:40:49.825
Happy birthday, Namking.

00:40:49.905 --> 00:40:54.345
I hope all your patients recover quickly.

00:40:54.425 --> 00:40:56.305
And I hope you don't get any new patients

00:40:56.385 --> 00:40:58.025
so you can finally get some rest.

00:40:59.385 --> 00:41:01.665
I like that. Thank you so much, Piang.

00:41:01.745 --> 00:41:04.505
That's the best birthday wish
I could ask for.

00:41:05.105 --> 00:41:07.905
By the way, when you said
you wanted me to rest,

00:41:07.985 --> 00:41:09.505
was it because you care about me,

00:41:09.585 --> 00:41:12.185
or because you don't want me
ditching you for work anymore?

00:41:14.585 --> 00:41:16.745
Actually, it's neither.

00:41:16.825 --> 00:41:18.105
I just

00:41:18.185 --> 00:41:22.105
thought it would sound cool to
wish a doctor something like that.

00:41:22.745 --> 00:41:24.825
You're very honest, aren't you?

00:41:25.465 --> 00:41:27.705
That's just how I am.

00:41:27.785 --> 00:41:29.905
Maybe we just don't know
each other that well yet.

00:41:31.705 --> 00:41:35.825
Then how about we get to know
each other better today?

00:41:35.905 --> 00:41:37.185
What do you think?

00:41:39.305 --> 00:41:40.145
Okay.

00:41:40.785 --> 00:41:42.425
Have you eaten yet?

00:41:42.505 --> 00:41:43.905
-Not yet.
-Let me show you around.

00:41:46.585 --> 00:41:48.025
What do you like?

00:41:48.105 --> 00:41:49.905
There are plenty of choices.

00:41:51.425 --> 00:41:54.345
-I'll just have some fruit.
-Sure.

00:41:56.305 --> 00:41:57.985
Very health-conscious.

00:42:14.385 --> 00:42:15.465
Song.

00:42:43.825 --> 00:42:44.745
Hello?

00:42:45.505 --> 00:42:47.385
Doctor, we have an emergency case.

00:42:47.985 --> 00:42:49.985
Okay, I'll be there right away.

00:42:50.065 --> 00:42:52.265
Please prepare the CT results
and the vital signs.

00:42:53.625 --> 00:42:55.345
Do you have an emergency?

00:42:55.425 --> 00:42:58.785
Yes. The hospital called
about an urgent case.

00:42:58.865 --> 00:43:00.105
Then why aren't you leaving?

00:43:01.105 --> 00:43:05.665
I promised my grandmother
that no matter what happened today,

00:43:05.745 --> 00:43:07.265
I'd stay until the party was over.

00:43:08.985 --> 00:43:10.905
It's okay. I'll take care of it.

00:43:12.185 --> 00:43:13.065
Let's go.

00:43:23.305 --> 00:43:24.945
What's wrong, Piang?

00:43:26.305 --> 00:43:27.825
I have a stomachache.

00:43:27.905 --> 00:43:30.665
So I'd like to ask your permission

00:43:30.745 --> 00:43:33.745
for Namking to take me to the hospital.

00:43:33.825 --> 00:43:36.865
Of course. Go on now,
and take good care of her.

00:43:36.945 --> 00:43:39.385
-Okay. I'll take her there right away.
-Alright.

00:43:39.465 --> 00:43:40.665
Thank you, Grandma.

00:44:24.985 --> 00:44:27.265
Thank you so much for helping me.

00:44:27.345 --> 00:44:29.425
So where are you going now?

00:44:30.425 --> 00:44:32.025
I honestly don't know.

00:44:33.745 --> 00:44:36.105
Can I hitch a ride
to the hospital with you?

00:44:36.865 --> 00:44:38.425
The hospital?

00:44:38.505 --> 00:44:40.465
That's hardly a place you'd visit for fun.

00:44:41.065 --> 00:44:42.265
That's okay.

00:44:42.345 --> 00:44:43.865
I can go anywhere.

00:44:45.065 --> 00:44:46.825
I just want to get out of here first.

00:44:47.425 --> 00:44:50.065
-Let's go. Aren't your patients waiting?
-Okay.

00:44:56.505 --> 00:44:58.905
This is the perk of having
a doctor as your girlfriend.

00:45:02.545 --> 00:45:03.785
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:45:03.865 --> 00:45:05.625
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:45:06.625 --> 00:45:09.945
My grandmother
is one of Dr. Namking's patients.

00:45:10.025 --> 00:45:13.145
She couldn't make it today,
so she asked me to bring this gift.

00:45:13.825 --> 00:45:15.225
Thank you very much.

00:45:15.905 --> 00:45:18.585
Namking said she had an urgent matter,
so she rushed off.

00:45:18.665 --> 00:45:20.945
What a pity you didn't get to meet her.

00:45:21.025 --> 00:45:22.545
Then I'll be on my way.

00:45:22.625 --> 00:45:23.825
Alright.

00:45:32.985 --> 00:45:33.985
Hey.

00:45:34.625 --> 00:45:36.385
Do you know that girl?

00:45:36.465 --> 00:45:37.785
Not really.

00:45:37.865 --> 00:45:40.665
She said she's the granddaughter
of one of Namking's patients.

00:45:41.345 --> 00:45:43.585
Her grandmother asked her
to bring the gift.

00:45:45.865 --> 00:45:48.065
Huh? Where did Piang go?

00:45:48.145 --> 00:45:50.225
-She said she had a stomachache.
-Huh?

00:45:50.305 --> 00:45:52.185
So I had Namking take her to the hospital.

00:45:53.105 --> 00:45:55.705
But honestly,
I don't think it's anything serious.

00:45:56.505 --> 00:45:57.865
She'll be back soon enough.

00:45:58.585 --> 00:46:00.665
-Don't they look adorable together?
-They do.

00:46:00.745 --> 00:46:02.345
They seem to get along really well.

00:46:03.265 --> 00:46:04.825
They take good care of each other.

00:46:20.585 --> 00:46:21.665
Grandma.

00:46:22.385 --> 00:46:23.745
You're still awake?

00:46:25.625 --> 00:46:27.665
What about Piang? Has she gone upstairs?

00:46:28.865 --> 00:46:30.825
She said her stomach hurt,

00:46:30.905 --> 00:46:32.945
but she seemed perfectly fine to me.

00:46:34.025 --> 00:46:35.025
Look.

00:46:35.105 --> 00:46:37.745
Piang and I went to
Namking's birthday party today.

00:46:39.105 --> 00:46:40.625
Look at your sister's face. See?

00:46:40.705 --> 00:46:42.625
She looks so happy.

00:46:45.745 --> 00:46:48.345
Grandma, can't you tell?

00:46:48.425 --> 00:46:50.985
That smile isn't coming
from her heart at all.

00:46:55.065 --> 00:46:56.145
I don't care.

00:46:56.825 --> 00:46:59.065
As long as she follows my wishes,

00:46:59.145 --> 00:47:01.665
it's better than chasing after that
useless researcher.

00:47:01.745 --> 00:47:03.105
That's enough for me.

00:47:04.665 --> 00:47:05.905
Right.

00:47:05.985 --> 00:47:08.345
You've never cared about anyone's feelings

00:47:08.425 --> 00:47:10.225
except your own.

00:47:15.785 --> 00:47:16.905
You've gotten bolder.

00:47:17.945 --> 00:47:20.905
Now you're even saying things
I don't want to hear.

00:47:21.585 --> 00:47:22.625
Why?

00:47:22.705 --> 00:47:26.385
Did something, or someone,
change you like that?

00:47:27.585 --> 00:47:31.465
Usually,
you don't really talk to anyone, do you?

00:47:35.145 --> 00:47:36.065
Hmm…

00:47:37.945 --> 00:47:38.945
That's right.

00:47:40.825 --> 00:47:42.625
I don't really talk to anyone.

00:47:43.945 --> 00:47:45.225
I'm used to it.

00:47:46.825 --> 00:47:50.945
Used to carrying everything on my own.

00:47:55.305 --> 00:47:56.785
The problems,

00:47:57.425 --> 00:47:59.265
everyone's expectations,

00:48:00.825 --> 00:48:02.145
Piang,

00:48:03.545 --> 00:48:04.745
Grandma,

00:48:06.305 --> 00:48:08.065
and everyone at the company.

00:48:13.265 --> 00:48:14.825
I have feelings too,

00:48:15.665 --> 00:48:17.745
but I've never told anyone.

00:48:30.665 --> 00:48:32.025
Actually,

00:48:33.025 --> 00:48:36.225
even if you don't talk to anyone,

00:48:37.025 --> 00:48:39.025
you can still feel lighter.

00:48:41.345 --> 00:48:45.305
You just need to put
your own peace of mind first.

00:48:46.465 --> 00:48:49.105
Don't care about what others want

00:48:49.665 --> 00:48:51.225
more than yourself.

00:48:55.225 --> 00:48:56.345
Not really.

00:48:56.905 --> 00:48:59.745
I just wanted to try being more like you.

00:49:00.425 --> 00:49:01.985
Caring less about other people

00:49:02.065 --> 00:49:03.665
and putting my own needs first.

00:49:04.385 --> 00:49:07.305
Maybe that would make me happier.

00:49:07.385 --> 00:49:08.425
Why?

00:49:08.985 --> 00:49:11.905
Were you really that unhappy before?

00:49:11.985 --> 00:49:15.025
Not really.
But I wasn't exactly happy either.

00:49:16.945 --> 00:49:17.825
Oh, right.

00:49:17.905 --> 00:49:21.025
Grandma, next week there's a competition

00:49:21.105 --> 00:49:22.945
to find the winner
of the Mega Excellent Award

00:49:23.025 --> 00:49:24.985
for Outstanding Researcher.

00:49:25.065 --> 00:49:26.905
I'd like to invite you to come watch.

00:49:27.505 --> 00:49:29.665
It's a competition between
Sarut and Sadanun.

00:49:30.265 --> 00:49:31.665
You'll see for yourself

00:49:31.745 --> 00:49:34.105
that Song isn't as useless as you think.

00:49:48.305 --> 00:49:50.745
Look, I even brought my lucky ribbon.

00:49:50.825 --> 00:49:51.985
You wear it every day.

00:49:52.945 --> 00:49:55.305
You really love teasing me.

00:49:55.385 --> 00:49:56.505
Good morning, Boss.

00:49:56.585 --> 00:49:57.705
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

00:50:01.785 --> 00:50:03.505
Go win this.

00:50:03.585 --> 00:50:05.425
Namprow. Ploy.

00:50:21.905 --> 00:50:22.745
Oh, Piang.

00:50:24.265 --> 00:50:25.825
Are you here to support Sadanun?

00:50:28.985 --> 00:50:31.145
-None of your business.
-Piang.

00:50:31.225 --> 00:50:32.745
You're younger.

00:50:32.825 --> 00:50:34.545
You shouldn't speak
so rudely to your elders.

00:50:38.385 --> 00:50:39.345
That goes both ways.

00:50:40.145 --> 00:50:43.225
Adults should behave in a way
that earns children's respect too.

00:50:46.185 --> 00:50:48.225
Let's go into the meeting room.

00:50:48.305 --> 00:50:49.385
It's almost time.

00:50:57.465 --> 00:50:58.665
Next,

00:50:58.745 --> 00:50:59.745
we'll begin the competition

00:50:59.825 --> 00:51:02.705
to determine this year's winner
of the Mega Excellent Award

00:51:02.785 --> 00:51:05.305
for Outstanding Researcher.

00:51:05.385 --> 00:51:08.145
The challenge is
What Does Love Taste Like?

00:51:08.225 --> 00:51:11.305
Create a dish that
captures the taste of love.

00:51:11.385 --> 00:51:12.345
According to the rules,

00:51:12.425 --> 00:51:14.705
Research Team A will present first.

00:51:14.785 --> 00:51:15.905
Please begin.

00:51:27.025 --> 00:51:28.305
-Hey.
-Hey.

00:51:33.225 --> 00:51:34.385
It's exactly the same.

00:51:34.465 --> 00:51:35.145
GRANDMA'S QUINOA CUP PORRIDGE

00:51:36.025 --> 00:51:37.945
Even the name is the same.

00:51:38.025 --> 00:51:39.865
This is A Cup of Care,

00:51:39.945 --> 00:51:41.865
Grandma's Quinoa Cup Porridge.

00:51:41.945 --> 00:51:45.425
I was inspired by the porridge

00:51:45.505 --> 00:51:47.025
my grandmother used to make for me.

00:51:47.625 --> 00:51:49.665
You've got some nerve.
Are you so desperate

00:51:49.745 --> 00:51:51.745
that you had to steal our work?

00:51:51.825 --> 00:51:53.665
Do you even have a brain
in that head of yours?

00:51:56.105 --> 00:51:59.625
Namprow, you can't make
accusations without proof.

00:51:59.705 --> 00:52:01.865
I'm not accusing anyone.
I'm stating the truth.

00:52:01.945 --> 00:52:04.945
My team and I built this project
from the ground up.

00:52:05.585 --> 00:52:06.505
Everyone,

00:52:06.585 --> 00:52:09.185
this project truly belongs to Team B.

00:52:10.665 --> 00:52:14.305
And the person who started
it was Sadanun. Understand?

00:52:14.385 --> 00:52:16.425
Then show us the evidence.

00:52:17.585 --> 00:52:18.825
We're researchers.

00:52:18.905 --> 00:52:21.065
Everyone here knows

00:52:21.145 --> 00:52:23.585
that empty words carry no weight.

00:52:25.105 --> 00:52:26.025
You've got some nerve.

00:52:32.065 --> 00:52:33.345
Piang.

00:52:33.945 --> 00:52:35.305
Sit down first.

00:52:36.185 --> 00:52:37.905
You want evidence, right?

00:52:41.905 --> 00:52:43.305
Bring that housekeeper in.

00:52:43.945 --> 00:52:44.865
Yes, Ma'am.

00:52:47.225 --> 00:52:48.265
What?

00:53:00.985 --> 00:53:02.025
This way, please.

00:53:08.625 --> 00:53:10.145
Tell them everything.

00:53:17.225 --> 00:53:18.345
Mr. Sarut

00:53:20.465 --> 00:53:24.465
really did steal Team B's project.

00:53:24.545 --> 00:53:25.825
Damn.

00:53:32.105 --> 00:53:33.505
And I'm the one

00:53:34.705 --> 00:53:36.025
who helped him.

00:53:39.865 --> 00:53:42.065
-Could you keep an eye on this?
-Sure.

00:53:42.145 --> 00:53:43.385
Okay.

00:53:44.385 --> 00:53:47.105
I'm sorry. Let me pick that up for you.

00:53:55.825 --> 00:53:56.985
Here.

00:54:03.065 --> 00:54:04.505
Thank you, Mr. Sarut.

00:54:38.865 --> 00:54:39.865
Hey.

00:54:40.465 --> 00:54:41.665
Don't frame me.

00:54:41.745 --> 00:54:42.705
Stop this right now.

00:54:45.905 --> 00:54:48.745
Don't stoop so low in my company.

00:54:51.905 --> 00:54:53.825
Why are you doing this to me?

00:54:54.825 --> 00:54:56.585
You don't like that woman either, do you?

00:54:56.665 --> 00:54:59.025
-You should be helping me bring her down.
-That's right.

00:54:59.785 --> 00:55:01.385
I may dislike someone,

00:55:02.265 --> 00:55:06.345
but for more than thirty years
that I've run this company,

00:55:06.945 --> 00:55:09.985
I've always stood by
what's right and fair.

00:55:10.905 --> 00:55:14.265
If someone is being dishonest,
no matter who the victim is,

00:55:14.345 --> 00:55:16.225
I will protect them.

00:55:16.905 --> 00:55:18.945
As for the person at fault,

00:55:19.025 --> 00:55:20.465
even if they're on my side,

00:55:20.545 --> 00:55:22.065
I will never take their side.

00:55:22.585 --> 00:55:24.385
No matter what,

00:55:24.465 --> 00:55:27.185
those who do wrong
must face the consequences.

00:55:35.065 --> 00:55:36.385
-Ma'am.
-Go.

00:55:37.425 --> 00:55:38.465
You may leave now.

00:55:38.545 --> 00:55:40.825
And don't ever set foot here again.

00:55:43.185 --> 00:55:44.585
This way, please.

00:56:05.505 --> 00:56:06.545
Everyone,

00:56:07.145 --> 00:56:09.185
since this has happened,

00:56:09.265 --> 00:56:12.385
I'd like to declare Team B the winner.

00:56:16.425 --> 00:56:18.905
And this year's
Outstanding Researcher Award

00:56:18.985 --> 00:56:20.425
-goes to…
-Wait.

00:56:25.985 --> 00:56:28.905
I'd like to hear Team B's presentation.

00:56:31.105 --> 00:56:32.785
Because I want to know

00:56:32.865 --> 00:56:34.505
just how capable they really are,

00:56:35.105 --> 00:56:38.185
and whether they truly deserve this award.

00:56:44.065 --> 00:56:47.305
A Cup of Care,
Grandma's Quinoa Cup Porridge.

00:56:47.385 --> 00:56:50.385
This dish is adapted
from a simple porridge

00:56:50.465 --> 00:56:52.585
that my grandmother often made for me

00:56:52.665 --> 00:56:54.705
whenever I was sad or stressed.

00:56:55.785 --> 00:56:57.385
I once asked my grandmother

00:56:58.105 --> 00:57:01.585
why she didn't just buy
something this simple instead.

00:57:01.665 --> 00:57:03.985
Why choose to spend the
time and effort making it herself?

00:57:05.225 --> 00:57:06.665
And she told me,

00:57:07.225 --> 00:57:08.785
"It's not just food.

00:57:08.865 --> 00:57:12.705
It's comfort and care,

00:57:12.785 --> 00:57:15.305
something a grandmother
wants to give her grandchild

00:57:15.385 --> 00:57:17.065
without needing any words."

00:57:19.585 --> 00:57:22.025
No, I want to go swimming.

00:57:22.105 --> 00:57:23.065
No.

00:57:24.145 --> 00:57:26.025
No, I want to go swimming.

00:57:26.105 --> 00:57:28.585
Piang, are you disobeying me?

00:57:28.665 --> 00:57:30.465
This isn't swimming time.

00:57:31.065 --> 00:57:33.905
Right now, you should be studying.

00:57:33.985 --> 00:57:36.185
-No, I want to go swimming.
-Piang.

00:57:36.265 --> 00:57:37.745
How dare you raise your voice at me?

00:57:41.785 --> 00:57:43.705
Grandma, you're mean.

00:57:56.065 --> 00:57:56.985
Where are you going?

00:57:58.665 --> 00:57:59.945
Go finish your studying.

00:58:00.825 --> 00:58:01.865
Yes, Grandma.

00:58:12.785 --> 00:58:14.305
Want another one?

00:58:15.545 --> 00:58:17.105
This is the last one.

00:58:19.985 --> 00:58:21.665
Cut its hair.

00:58:21.745 --> 00:58:23.225
It's about to pass out.

00:58:23.305 --> 00:58:25.545
-It'll die.
-Die?

00:58:25.625 --> 00:58:27.065
Put the glasses on first.

00:58:27.145 --> 00:58:28.625
Put the glasses on.

00:58:28.705 --> 00:58:30.145
Use this one.

00:58:31.025 --> 00:58:33.025
That's it. It's a small one.

00:58:33.105 --> 00:58:34.945
-Nun.
-Yes?

00:58:38.025 --> 00:58:39.545
Make something for Mud and Piang too.

00:58:39.625 --> 00:58:41.385
-Not for me.
-Okay.

00:58:50.025 --> 00:58:51.145
Hurry up.

00:58:51.225 --> 00:58:53.025
Try examining this one.

00:58:53.105 --> 00:58:54.185
Sis.

00:58:55.305 --> 00:58:57.905
Check it out. Give it a health check.

00:58:57.985 --> 00:58:59.185
And put glasses on it too.

00:58:59.265 --> 00:59:00.145
Put glasses on it.

00:59:22.225 --> 00:59:23.465
Madam Chairwoman.

00:59:29.945 --> 00:59:32.225
Thank you so much
for what you did about Sarut.

00:59:32.305 --> 00:59:33.305
No need.

00:59:34.105 --> 00:59:36.705
I told you, I do everything
for what's right.

00:59:38.305 --> 00:59:41.905
But if you think
what I did means that much,

00:59:42.825 --> 00:59:45.225
then I'd like something in return.

00:59:45.905 --> 00:59:48.425
When I warned you to stay away from Piang,

00:59:48.505 --> 00:59:49.425
perhaps it wasn't enough.

00:59:50.545 --> 00:59:53.105
But at Dr. Namking's birthday party,
you've probably see,

00:59:53.945 --> 00:59:57.465
where you and Piang stand is different.

00:59:58.185 --> 00:59:59.145
Therefore,

00:59:59.945 --> 01:00:01.705
stay away from my granddaughter.

01:00:03.905 --> 01:00:07.545
Like I said, I wasn't the one
who approached Piang first.

01:00:07.625 --> 01:00:09.625
She's the one who keeps coming after me.

01:00:09.705 --> 01:00:11.145
Then run.

01:00:11.865 --> 01:00:13.305
Run even farther away.

01:00:13.385 --> 01:00:16.185
-I've already tried.
-It's not enough.

01:00:16.985 --> 01:00:19.545
Because Piang still hasn't let go of you.

01:00:31.385 --> 01:00:35.625
Alright. Then I'll try harder than before.

01:00:36.505 --> 01:00:38.305
And if that's still not enough,

01:00:39.665 --> 01:00:41.745
then I'll disappear from Piang's life.

01:00:49.785 --> 01:00:52.105
Song, you don't have to go that far.

01:01:04.065 --> 01:01:06.065
I'll be the one to leave.

01:02:03.865 --> 01:02:05.225
Hello, Song.

01:02:05.305 --> 01:02:06.665
Piang has disappeared.

01:02:07.705 --> 01:02:09.025
What is this woman to you?

01:02:12.105 --> 01:02:13.705
Grandma, did you have someone follow me?

01:02:13.785 --> 01:02:15.145
Do you care that much about Song?

01:02:15.225 --> 01:02:16.585
Are you upset with me?

01:02:18.625 --> 01:02:21.105
I think you know the
problem isn't her grandmother.

01:02:21.185 --> 01:02:22.345
The problem

01:02:22.425 --> 01:02:25.465
is that you refuse to
move on from your past.

01:02:26.985 --> 01:02:29.185
And if it starts with you,

01:02:29.265 --> 01:02:31.945
then you're the one who has to fix it.